t <- seq(1,nrow(dados),1)
t2 <- t^2
t3 <- t^3
sin365 <- sin(2*pi*t/365)
cos365 <- cos(2*pi*t/365)
library(season)

p <- data.frame(peri(dados$Deaths-modTen$fitted.values,adjmean=TRUE,plot=TRUE))

newdata<-data.frame(t=t,t2=t2,t3=t3,sin365=sin365,cos365=cos365)
head(newdata)
##   t t2  t3     sin365    cos365
## 1 1  1   1 0.01721336 0.9998518
## 2 2  4   8 0.03442161 0.9994074
## 3 3  9  27 0.05161967 0.9986668

## 5 5 25 125 0.08596480 0.9962982
## 6 6 36 216 0.10310170 0.9946708
esperado <- data.frame("fit"=predict(mod,newdata,interval="prediction",level = 0.95)[,1],
                       "lwr95"=predict(mod,newdata,interval="prediction",level = 0.95)[,2],
                       "upr95"=predict(mod,newdata,interval="prediction",level = 0.95)[,3],
                       "lwr99"=predict(mod,newdata,interval="prediction",level = 0.99)[,2],
                       "upr99"=predict(mod,newdata,interval="prediction",level = 0.99)[,3])
head(esperado)

lines(esperado$upr95~dados$Date,col="orange",lwd=2)

lines(esperado$lwr95~dados$Date,col="green",lwd=2)
lines(esperado$lwr99~dados$Date,col="darkgreen",lwd=2)

base <- data.frame("Data"=dados$Date,"Deaths"=dados$Deaths,
                   "Esperado"=esperado$fit,"LimiteSuperior95"=esperado$upr95)

head(base)

base$Deaths_new <- ifelse(base$Deaths<base$LimiteSuperior95,
                            base$Deaths,NA)
mod1 <- lm(base$Deaths_new ~ t + t2 + t3 + sin365+cos365)

                    "LimiteSuperior99"=esperado1$upr99)

base1$excesso <- ifelse(base1$Deaths<base1$LimiteSuperior95,
                        0,base1$Deaths-base1$Esperado)
plot(base1$Deaths~base1$Date,type="l",main="Daily Mortality in Portugal \n all causes 2009 to 2019",
     ylab="Deaths",xlab="Date",las=1,ylim=c(-70,800),axes=F)
axis.Date(1,at=seq(min(base1$Date),max(base1$Date)+1,by="6 months"),format="%m-%Y",cex.axis=0.6)
axis(2,seq(0,500,50))

lines(esperado1$lwr95~base1$Date,col="green",lwd=2,lty=2)
lines(esperado1$lwr99~base1$Date,col="darkgreen",lwd=2,lty=2)
par(new=T)
plot(base1$excesso~base1$Date,type="h",ylim=c(0,500),col="grey",axes=F,ylab="",xlab="")
axis(4,seq(0,160,20),col="grey")

base2 <- subset(base1,base1$Date>="2018-08-01" & base1$Date<="2018-08-10")
